\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Write 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
cov(G_{c},S_{c}) & =cov(\bar{G}+\varepsilon^{G},\bar{S}+\varepsilon^{S})\nonumber \\
 & =cov(\bar{G},\bar{S})+cov(\varepsilon^{G},\bar{S})+cov(\bar{G},\varepsilon^{S})+cov(\varepsilon^{G},\varepsilon^{S}).\label{eq:cov-with-error}
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For any 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $cov(X,Y)$
\end_inset

 is bounded by 
\begin_inset Formula $\sqrt{var(X)var(Y)}$
\end_inset

.
 Plugging 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{G}^{2}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{S}^{2}$
\end_inset

 into this formula shows that under condition 1, 
\begin_inset Formula $cov(G_{c},S_{c})$
\end_inset

 will be arbitrarily close to 
\begin_inset Formula $cov(\bar{G},\bar{S})$
\end_inset

.
 Similarly, writing
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
var(G_{c})=var(\bar{G})+var(\varepsilon^{G})+2cov(\bar{G},\varepsilon^{G})
\]

\end_inset

shows that 
\begin_inset Formula $var(G_{c})$
\end_inset

 will approach 
\begin_inset Formula $var(\bar{G})$
\end_inset

 as 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{G}^{2}$
\end_inset

 grows small, and similarly for 
\begin_inset Formula $var(S_{c})$
\end_inset

.
 Plugging these facts into (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:corr-cov-var"

\end_inset

) shows that 
\begin_inset Formula $corr(G_{c},S_{c})$
\end_inset

 approaches 
\begin_inset Formula $corr(\bar{G},\bar{S})$
\end_inset

 as 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{G}^{2}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{S}^{2}$
\end_inset

 grow small.
 Proposition 1 then shows 
\begin_inset Formula $corr(\bar{G},\bar{S})<corr(G_{p},S_{p})$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $k\in(0,1)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

